 Poster Recreation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The film screening took place at the Media Lab, where 54 students gathered to watch &#39;Irakal,&#39; a film directed by KG George. The choice of &#39;Irakal&#39; was a fitting homage to the renowned director and added a cultural and educational dimension to the event.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Simultaneously, the Poster Recreation activity unfolded at the Department of Digital Film Production, attracting seven students from various departments of the college. This creative endeavor showcased the interdisciplinary nature of cinema appreciation and participation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The event was graced by esteemed personalities of the college. Prof Dr. A Biju, Principal of MES Asmabi College has inaugurated the event. The greeting has delivered by Dr. KP Sumedhan, Director of Self Financing Courses and Mynag Suresh, Head of the Department of Digital Film delivered the Welcome speech. Maneesha, a faculty member from the Department of Digital Film Production, expressed gratitude and appreciation, extending thanks on behalf of the organizing team.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','4','52',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'50','2','Competition','Recent','14',NULL,'2023-11-17 06:58:59',2,2,0,50,2,0,0,8,0,40,NULL,'31','615',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Experiancial',NULL,NULL,'https://www.instagram.com/p/CyTWd8fyjCt/',NULL,NULL,'Recent','1700204278.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0'),(1450,113,'‘PLANET REELS’ DOCUMENTARY SCREENING : \'GUARDIANS OF THE AMAZON’ ON WORLD ENVIRONMENT DAY','2023-06-05','2023-06-05','MEDIA LAB','‘PLANET REELS’ DOCUMENTARY SCREENING : \'GUARDIANS OF THE AMAZON’ ON WORLD ENVIRONMENT DAY AT MES ASMABI COLLEGE','<p><strong>Department of Digital Film Production celebrated World Environment Day by organizing a documentary screening event called &#39;Plant Reels.&#39; The venue was the Media Lab at MES Asmabi College, P. Vemballur. The event aimed to create awareness among the college community about environmental issues in the Amazon rainforest, with a focus on the documentary &#39;Guardians of Amazon.&#39;</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Rasidha MS, the Staff Coordinator, delivered the welcome speech, emphasizing the significance of World Environment Day and the importance of the documentary screening. Mynag Suresh, the Head of the Department of Digital Film Production, delivered the Presidential address, urging students to become environmental guardians.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Prof Dr. A Biju, the Principal of MES Asmabi College, inaugurated the event, highlighting the role of the Amazon rainforest in maintaining ecological balance. Dr. Sanand Sadanandan, the Head of the Political Science Department, delivered a presentation on the environmental challenges faced by the rainforest, emphasizing its biodiversity and the role of local communities in conservation.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>The screening of &#39;Guardians of Amazon&#39; depicted the struggles and triumphs of activists fighting to protect the rainforest. It showcased the devastating impacts of deforestation and mining on biodiversity and indigenous cultures. The documentary inspired the audience to take action.</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','4','42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'40','2','Other','Recent','15',NULL,'2023-11-17 07:05:01',2,2,0,40,2,0,0,8,0,30,NULL,'31','615',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Other',NULL,NULL,'https://www.instagram.com/p/CtEy8mvSX8O/',NULL,NULL,'Recent','1700204788.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0'),(1451,143,'SHORT FILM SCREENING','2023-08-22','2023-08-22','MEDIA LAB','On August 22nd 2023 Tuesday we have conducted short film screening at media lab.More than 15 short films made by 5th semester students were screened. Our Alumnus and then university 1st Rank Holder Ms.Nizri MK (Information Assistant,PR Dept Kerala) inaugurated the function.She shared her inspiring journey as a film festival curator and such stories to our students. “Reve” directe